column5: Hooked up with a couple buddies and did some perching. Nice weather, a good number of boats out but not crowded. On the water about 10:00 and fished till about 2:00, jigging wasn't the greatest and we had the best luck with pickeral rigs (Lotta doubles). Not too many jumbos and put back a lot small ones, but kept enough for a good feed. We did OK and had a good time...   Biggest I got 11ins.
Nice chunky fish!! Was a great day for it too.  dsn
Great ! We are going this weekend can't wait!!!!!!
Hmmmm... I wonder if a fish can still be entered when OFC Community is spelt incorrectly... Survey says? LOL just joking brother!  nice feed!  Gerritt
